Hey <@UMZFZHVUJ>,
the grinch gets all the cookies today :smile:

In all seriousness:
• If it's the HubSpot cookie banner and it's apperently "not working", you can test it with this code:
```// replace '.cookie-banner-button' with the class of your cookie button class 
document.querySelectorAll('.cookie-banner-button').forEach(button =&gt; {
    button.addEventListener('click', function() {
      (function(){
        var _hsp = window._hsp = window._hsp || [];
        _hsp.push(['showBanner']);
        })()
    });
  });```
• if they're using some other implementation like OneTrust - they have to check the settings there. Here's a list of all available <https://knowledge.HubSpot.com/privacy-and-consent/what-cookies-does-HubSpot-set-in-a-visitor-s-browser|HS cookies>
• If they have something like "GTM triggering the cookie banner", this might be related to this aswell(and I advise every client against this) . In this case the user has to enable Marketing cookies since GTM will fall under the Marketing cookie category. In other words: If the user won't enable marketing cookies, the cookie banner won't appear since it will be triggered by GTM - which will be blocked since the marketing cookies are not accepted....
